"{\"Course Name\": \"INTRODUCTION TO CORPORATE SUSTAINABILITY\", \"Course Level\": \"210X\", \"Dept Abbreviation\": \"BUS\", \"Course Description\": \"This course will cover the basics of corporate environmental sustainability with some introduction of social sustainability. The world has come under increasing environmental and social pressures. Corporations strategically and operationally influence the natural environment and social systems. We will offer the theory and practice of how organizations need to function to help decouple economic well-being from environmental degradation. Topics will include building sustainability strategy, green marketing and finance, sustainable supply chains, sustainability performance measurement and monitoring, and other emergent topics.\\r\\nRecommended Background: None\", \"Requirements\": [], \"Is Cat 1\": true, \"Start Year For Cat 2\": -1}"